00:35:06.273 --> 00:35:07.608
- Oops.
- [urinating stops]

705
00:35:24.458 --> 00:35:25.792
[groans]

706
00:35:28.754 --> 00:35:31.173
[tap running. stops]

707
00:35:38.013 --> 00:35:40.098
[chattering.
laughing in distance]

708
00:35:45.812 --> 00:35:49.566
[drawer opens. closes]

709
00:36:04.248 --> 00:36:08.418
[breathes deeply]

710
00:36:20.097 --> 00:36:22.473
[person 1 on television] <i>We
don't know how she was killed.</i>

711
00:36:22.474 --> 00:36:23.724
<i>I think the weapon...</i>

712
00:36:23.725 --> 00:36:26.045
[person 2 on television] <i>She
was struck with a candlestick.</i>

713
00:36:26.353 --> 00:36:28.355
[person 1] <i>A candlestick?
Are you sure?</i>

714
00:36:28.856 --> 00:36:30.065
[person 2] <i>A heavy silver one.</i>

715
00:36:30.899 --> 00:36:33.526
- [person 1] <i>How can you know?</i>
<i>- Microscope.</i>

716
00:36:33.527 --> 00:36:35.612
[Coop playing drums]

717
00:36:40.325 --> 00:36:41.827
Here. Just...

718
00:36:45.163 --> 00:36:46.163
[chimes]

719
00:36:51.086 --> 00:36:53.171
One of you guys wanna trade
cars for a little while?

720
00:36:53.172 --> 00:36:54.172
Fuck yeah.

721
00:37:10.230 --> 00:37:11.231
[grunts]

722
00:37:24.578 --> 00:37:25.787
[doorknob rattles]

723
00:37:37.799 --> 00:37:41.094
[chattering. laughing. echoing]

724
00:37:52.814 --> 00:37:54.815
[toilet flushes]

725
00:37:54.816 --> 00:37:55.733
- Fuck!
- Jesus.

726
00:37:55.734 --> 00:37:59.195
- [Tori] Daddy!
- What the... Oh. for God's sake!

727
00:37:59.196 --> 00:38:01.156
Fucking unbelievable.

728
00:38:06.828 --> 00:38:07.829
[grunts]

729
00:38:08.914 --> 00:38:10.873
- Mr. Cooper.
- Go away. Jake.

730
00:38:10.874 --> 00:38:13.376
Sorry. sir. We didn't know
you were gonna be here.

731
00:38:13.377 --> 00:38:15.002
- swear to G... [grunts] Fuck.
- [grunts]

732
00:38:15.003 --> 00:38:17.797
- Daddy! What did you do? Oh. my God.
- [groaning]

733
00:38:17.798 --> 00:38:19.841
- I told you to stop calling me sir.
- [Tori] Are you okay?

734
00:38:19.842 --> 00:38:21.092
[cell phone ringing]

735
00:38:21.093 --> 00:38:22.969
- What the fuck is wrong with you?
- [Jake groaning]

736
00:38:22.970 --> 00:38:24.929
- [Tori] Oh. my God. Dad.
- I gotta take this. Hey.

737
00:38:24.930 --> 00:38:28.891
- [crying] Punched me in the... [groaning]
- No. Bruce. I'm sorry. What?

738
00:38:28.892 --> 00:38:31.477
- What can I do? What do you need?
- Oh. God. Yeah.

739
00:38:31.478 --> 00:38:33.813
- I mean. I can be there in ten minutes.
- [Tori] Are you insane?

740
00:38:33.814 --> 00:38:35.731
[Coop] Yeah. sorry
about this. Bye.

741
00:38:35.732 --> 00:38:39.694
Just... Put some ice on it
or something. It'll be fine.

742
00:38:39.695 --> 00:38:40.695
[grunts]

743
00:38:40.696 --> 00:38:42.029
- [whimpers]
- [car door closes]

744
00:38:42.030 --> 00:38:43.823
["Fake Plastic Trees" playing]

745
00:38:43.824 --> 00:38:47.452
[singer] <i>♪ Looks
like the real thing ♪</i>

746
00:38:50.372 --> 00:38:54.877
<i>♪ You taste like
the real thing ♪</i>

747
00:38:55.752 --> 00:39:01.008
<i>♪ My fake plastic love ♪</i>

748
00:39:06.013 --> 00:39:07.013
Hey. Bruce.

749
00:39:07.014 --> 00:39:08.931
- Thanks for coming. Coop.
- [Coop] You know it.

750
00:39:08.932 --> 00:39:12.352
[singer] <i>♪ But I can't
help the feeling ♪</i>

751
00:39:14.897 --> 00:39:19.318
<i>♪ I could blow
through the ceiling ♪</i>

752
00:39:20.611 --> 00:39:26.241
<i>♪ If I could just turn and run ♪</i>

753
00:39:28.243 --> 00:39:29.243
Hey. Andy.

754
00:39:30.329 --> 00:39:31.537
Bruce called me.

755
00:39:31.538 --> 00:39:32.873
Yeah. I figured he would.

756
00:39:33.874 --> 00:39:35.459
I could use the
ride home anyway.

757
00:39:36.126 --> 00:39:37.126
How did you get here?

758
00:39:37.127 --> 00:39:38.295
I walked.

759
00:39:38.921 --> 00:39:39.921
You off your meds again?

760
00:39:40.756 --> 00:39:42.633
Just wanted to feel
something. you know?

761
00:39:43.425 --> 00:39:44.425
How you feel?

762
00:39:45.427 --> 00:39:47.720
- Shitty. actually. [chuckles]
- Hmm.

763
00:39:47.721 --> 00:39:48.804
How was your day?

764
00:39:48.805 --> 00:39:51.099
Oh. The same.

765
00:39:51.683 --> 00:39:54.144
You don't look so great.
and that's coming from me.

766
00:39:54.770 --> 00:39:56.021
Come on. Let's get you home.

767
00:39:58.148 --> 00:39:59.149
[Coop grunts]

768
00:40:01.401 --> 00:40:02.235
[sighs]

769
00:40:02.236 --> 00:40:03.695
[singer breathes deeply]

770
00:40:05.113 --> 00:40:06.447
He still loves me. you know.

771
00:40:06.448 --> 00:40:08.199
Honey. he's got a
wife and two kids.

772
00:40:08.200 --> 00:40:09.701
Well. everybody's got something.

773
00:40:10.202 --> 00:40:12.453
What're you playing there?
The Smashing Pumpkins?

774
00:40:12.454 --> 00:40:16.415
Um. Radiohead.
dipshit. [chuckles]

775
00:40:16.416 --> 00:40:19.253
Right. right. Of
course. Come on.

776
00:40:24.091 --> 00:40:25.092
Hey.

777
00:40:28.637 --> 00:40:29.638
You'll be all right.

778
00:40:32.975 --> 00:40:34.601
Give me this. Get in.

779
00:40:38.313 --> 00:40:39.940
- New car?
- It's a loaner.

780
00:40:40.440 --> 00:40:43.777
- Don't give me any shit.
- [chuckles]

781
00:40:52.953 --> 00:40:54.580
[exhales deeply]

782
00:40:56.707 --> 00:40:58.000
I'm in trouble. Ali.

783
00:40:59.793 --> 00:41:00.793
How bad?

784
00:41:02.462 --> 00:41:05.716
I might need you to give up the apartment
and move back in with Mom and Dad.

785
00:41:07.509 --> 00:41:08.510
Well. sucks for them.

786
00:41:10.888 --> 00:41:12.597
Yeah. It will if you
don't take your meds.

787
00:41:12.598 --> 00:41:14.474
I make no promises.

788
00:41:17.227 --> 00:41:19.353
- This car smells like ass.
- God. I know.

789
00:41:19.354 --> 00:41:21.398
- It's like something died in it.
- [engine starts]

790
00:41:31.783 --> 00:41:33.785
[pedestrians chattering]

791
00:41:43.128 --> 00:41:45.047
Liv. Liv.

792
00:41:46.006 --> 00:41:48.424
Just... Please let me
talk to you for a second.

793
00:41:48.425 --> 00:41:51.552
[sighs] Look... Look. I'm really
sorry about what happened to you.

794
00:41:51.553 --> 00:41:52.888
It sucks that they fired you.

795
00:41:54.890 --> 00:41:57.266
- Do you really feel that way?
- Of course I do.

796
00:41:57.267 --> 00:41:59.770
Well then. can you please
withdraw your complaint?

797
00:42:00.354 --> 00:42:03.272
I mean. you c... you can recant and
indemnify Bailey against a lawsuit.

798
00:42:03.273 --> 00:42:05.149
- I can get my job back.
- What?

799
00:42:05.150 --> 00:42:09.070
Look. I'm sorry if I mishandled
things with you in any way.

800
00:42:09.071 --> 00:42:10.780
I just thought we were
both having a good time.

801
00:42:10.781 --> 00:42:12.907
Wait. Stop. Just stop. I-I...

802
00:42:12.908 --> 00:42:14.701
I don't know what
you're talking about.

803
00:42:16.495 --> 00:42:18.497
I never filed a complaint.

804
00:42:19.748 --> 00:42:20.958
[elevator bell dings]

805
00:42:31.802 --> 00:42:33.469
[receptionist] Coop.
He's on a call.

806
00:42:33.470 --> 00:42:34.680
It's o... It's okay. Mary.

807
00:42:36.598 --> 00:42:39.267
- There was never any complaint.
- Coop. You can't be here.

808
00:42:39.268 --> 00:42:40.935
Liv Cross never
filed a complaint.

809
00:42:40.936 --> 00:42:42.728
It's an HR issue. I
only know what I'm told.

810
00:42:42.729 --> 00:42:43.980
Bullshit. Jack. You did this.

811
00:42:43.981 --> 00:42:46.232
You broke company policy.
My hands were tied.

812
00:42:46.233 --> 00:42:48.833
You saw an opportunity to take my
book and you decided to fuck me.

813
00:42:49.528 --> 00:42:50.570
You fucked yourself.

814
00:42:50.571 --> 00:42:51.697
I thought we were friends.

815
00:42:55.033 --> 00:42:57.159
At least let me keep my
fucking capital account.

816
00:42:57.160 --> 00:42:59.871
[stammers] I'm begging you. That's
my money. I need that money.

817
00:42:59.872 --> 00:43:01.582
- No. it isn't.
- [knocks on door]

818
00:43:03.292 --> 00:43:06.879
Your biggest mistake was thinking
any of this was ever yours.

819
00:43:07.754 --> 00:43:08.964
All right. all right.

820
00:43:13.093 --> 00:43:15.095
It's not yours if
you can't keep it.

821
00:43:26.440 --> 00:43:27.649
[screams]

822
00:43:35.949 --> 00:43:38.789
[person 1 on television] <i>I just can't
let you ruin that beautiful motor.</i>

823
00:43:38.994 --> 00:43:40.120
<i>Okay. start her up.</i>

824
00:43:45.959 --> 00:43:47.294
[cell phone buzzes]

825
00:43:52.633 --> 00:43:53.926
[sighs]

826
00:44:03.227 --> 00:44:04.645
[exhales deeply]

827
00:44:06.939 --> 00:44:07.940
- Here.
- Ooh.

828
00:44:09.233 --> 00:44:10.234
[grunts]

829
00:44:20.494 --> 00:44:22.120
How is Tori's boyfriend?

830
00:44:24.581 --> 00:44:26.917
- Jake?
- That's correct.

831
00:44:28.335 --> 00:44:29.377
He'll survive.

832
00:44:29.378 --> 00:44:31.630
Hmm. And Tori?

833
00:44:32.589 --> 00:44:33.590
[clicks tongue]

834
00:44:34.341 --> 00:44:36.885
You gotta give it a couple
more days. I'm working on it.

835
00:44:43.100 --> 00:44:44.351
You're not yourself. Coop.

836
00:44:45.394 --> 00:44:46.894
[sighs]

837
00:44:46.895 --> 00:44:50.106
Look. I'm sorry about the barbecue.
I was a little overserved.

838
00:44:50.107 --> 00:44:52.859
I'm not talking about the barbecue.
and I'm not talking about the fact

839
00:44:52.860 --> 00:44:54.527
that you assaulted our
daughter's boyfriend.

840
00:44:54.528 --> 00:44:56.738
- Although. Jesus Christ.
- What then?

841
00:44:58.448 --> 00:44:59.532
I don't know.

842
00:44:59.533 --> 00:45:01.285
You just seem so...

843
00:45:02.369 --> 00:45:03.370
alone.

844
00:45:04.705 --> 00:45:06.914
Yeah. well. I live
here. and you...

845
00:45:06.915 --> 00:45:09.876
[inhales deeply] ...live there
in our house with our kids.

846
00:45:09.877 --> 00:45:12.796
- I know.
- You left me. That would make me...

847
00:45:14.965 --> 00:45:15.882
alone. [sighs]

848
00:45:15.883 --> 00:45:17.718
That's not what I'm
talking about though.

849
00:45:19.720 --> 00:45:20.971
I'm worried about you.

850
00:45:22.139 --> 00:45:23.140
[sighs]

851
00:45:26.685 --> 00:45:27.686
Hey.

852
00:45:29.521 --> 00:45:30.814
What is it?

853
00:45:33.692 --> 00:45:35.903
Now. come on. You can still
talk to me. can't you?

854
00:45:39.448 --> 00:45:40.449
I'm fine.

855
00:45:42.034 --> 00:45:45.579
I am. [stammers]
I'm finding my way.

856
00:45:49.458 --> 00:45:50.459
[chuckles]

857
00:45:53.962 --> 00:45:54.963
Okay.

858
00:45:57.925 --> 00:45:58.926
[Coop sighs]

859
00:46:01.053 --> 00:46:02.054
Fair enough.

860
00:46:10.145 --> 00:46:11.396
Thanks for coming by.

861
00:46:12.856 --> 00:46:13.857
Thanks for the beer.

862
00:46:22.449 --> 00:46:23.450
Miss Cross.

863
00:46:24.785 --> 00:46:27.787
- How can I help you?
- I was hoping for an explanation.

864
00:46:27.788 --> 00:46:29.080
The Andrew Cooper thing.

865
00:46:29.081 --> 00:46:30.498
I didn't file a complaint.

866
00:46:30.499 --> 00:46:33.709
Somebody reported your
involvement to HR.

867
00:46:33.710 --> 00:46:36.128
- But there was no complaint.
- Whiskey?

868
00:46:36.129 --> 00:46:37.798
- No.
- Sit.

869
00:46:41.218 --> 00:46:44.554
I'm sorry that it was phrased
like that. but complaint or not.

870
00:46:44.555 --> 00:46:48.307
Mr. Cooper was in direct violation
of our company's code of conduct.

871
00:46:48.308 --> 00:46:49.642
He's in a position of power.

872
00:46:49.643 --> 00:46:52.311
and we take our
protections very seriously.

873
00:46:52.312 --> 00:46:54.272
He's nowhere on my org chart.

874
00:46:54.273 --> 00:46:55.940
I don't report to anyone
who reports to him.

875
00:46:55.941 --> 00:46:58.360
Does that mean he couldn't
get you fired if he so chose?

876
00:46:58.986 --> 00:47:01.320
- He didn't need to lose his job.
- Hmm.

877
00:47:01.321 --> 00:47:04.908
I've got a conference room full of
labor lawyers who say otherwise.

878
00:47:09.496 --> 00:47:12.456
Shepherd tells me that you're a star.
He wants to put you up for promotion.

879
00:47:12.457 --> 00:47:15.042
He wants you running your own
desk. Are you ready for that?

880
00:47:15.043 --> 00:47:17.003
How is that related to this?

881
00:47:17.004 --> 00:47:18.804
Oh. I'm done with this.
I've moved on to that.

882
00:47:19.506 --> 00:47:23.594
I'm more interested in your
future than Coop's past.

883
00:47:28.223 --> 00:47:30.558
I'll tell you what. I've got
a phone call in a minute.

884
00:47:30.559 --> 00:47:33.853
but let's do dinner later
in the week and discuss.

885
00:47:33.854 --> 00:47:35.439
Mary will check your avails.

886
00:47:36.148 --> 00:47:37.858
Shouldn't Shepherd join us?

887
00:47:40.235 --> 00:47:41.820
Shepherd's welcome to join.

888
00:47:45.407 --> 00:47:46.240
Thank you.

889
00:47:46.241 --> 00:47:48.327
["What Would You Call
Yourself" playing]

890
00:48:02.883 --> 00:48:04.885
[film noir on television]

891
00:48:30.244 --> 00:48:31.453
[basketball thuds]

892
00:48:42.297 --> 00:48:43.966
[song intensifies]

893
00:48:54.226 --> 00:48:57.688
[both exclaiming]

894
00:49:46.111 --> 00:49:47.112
[song ends]

895
00:49:49.364 --> 00:49:51.199
[Diane] Okay. uh. do
you have everything...

896
00:49:51.200 --> 00:49:52.950
[Coop] <i>Viewed from a
certain perspective.</i>

897
00:49:52.951 --> 00:49:56.330
<i>life boils down to a series
of interconnected decisions.</i>

898
00:49:56.914 --> 00:49:58.790
<i>The Millers decided
to go to Belize.</i>

899
00:50:01.001 --> 00:50:02.669
<i>I decided to go to the Millers'.</i>

900
00:50:08.884 --> 00:50:11.511
<i>Westmont Village has its
own private security patrol.</i>

901
00:50:11.512 --> 00:50:13.639
<i>as well as the Westmont
police department.</i>

902
00:50:14.389 --> 00:50:16.558
<i>The crime rate is
almost nonexistent.</i>

903
00:50:18.393 --> 00:50:20.228
<i>You live in a place
like that long enough.</i>

904
00:50:20.229 --> 00:50:22.689
<i>you start to feel insulated
from the rest of the world.</i>

905
00:50:23.440 --> 00:50:26.527
<i>You get complacent about
things like alarm systems</i>

906
00:50:27.236 --> 00:50:28.695
<i>and locking all your doors.</i>

907
00:51:16.243 --> 00:51:18.911
<i>The Patek Philippe Nautilus:
sealed 18-karat white gold.</i>

908
00:51:18.912 --> 00:51:19.996
<i>blue sunburst dial.</i>

909
00:51:19.997 --> 00:51:23.666
<i>water-resistant up to 30 meters.
like that will ever come up.</i>

910
00:51:23.667 --> 00:51:27.003
<i>Like the ads say. "You never
actually own a Patek Philippe.</i>

911
00:51:27.004 --> 00:51:29.590
<i>you merely look after it
for the next generation."</i>

912
00:51:32.134 --> 00:51:34.427
<i>Well. the next generation
tells time on their phones.</i>

913
00:51:34.428 --> 00:51:36.387
<i>so I figured no one was
gonna miss this one.</i>

914
00:51:36.388 --> 00:51:37.514
[drawer closes]

915
00:51:42.019 --> 00:51:43.228
[doorbell rings]

916
00:51:45.606 --> 00:51:48.609
[breathing heavily]

917
00:51:51.486 --> 00:51:53.030
[police radio chatter]

918
00:51:59.369 --> 00:52:00.996
[doorbell rings]

919
00:52:18.847 --> 00:52:20.640
Hi. guys. Is-Is.
uh. everything okay?

920
00:52:20.641 --> 00:52:22.642
Good evening. sir.
You live here?

921
00:52:22.643 --> 00:52:23.976
Yeah. yeah. I sure do.

922
00:52:23.977 --> 00:52:26.187
[officer] Your house was placed on
a vacation watch starting tonight.

923
00:52:26.188 --> 00:52:29.398
We saw the Honda parked down the
street. the lights on in the house...

924
00:52:29.399 --> 00:52:30.567
figured we'd check in.

925
00:52:31.985 --> 00:52:34.195
[sighs] That's my son's car.

926
00:52:34.196 --> 00:52:36.614
I told him to pull it into
the garage before we left.

927
00:52:36.615 --> 00:52:37.907
So you are going on vacation?

928
00:52:37.908 --> 00:52:39.867
Oh. yeah. Bright and
early tomorrow morning.

929
00:52:39.868 --> 00:52:42.578
My wife must've given you the
wrong date when she called it in.

930
00:52:42.579 --> 00:52:46.165
- No worries. Have a great trip.
- [sighs] Thanks. you guys.

931
00:52:46.166 --> 00:52:47.668
I appreciate it.

932
00:52:53.257 --> 00:52:54.675
[sighs]

933
00:52:56.093 --> 00:52:59.263
[breathing deeply]

934
00:53:01.181 --> 00:53:04.184
[laughing]

935
00:53:07.771 --> 00:53:09.272
<i>I don't know what
I was thinking.</i>

936
00:53:09.273 --> 00:53:10.565
<i>Well. that's not true.</i>

937
00:53:10.566 --> 00:53:13.651
<i>I was thinking that Peter and
Diane Miller were assholes.</i>

938
00:53:13.652 --> 00:53:15.320
<i>and they didn't
deserve all of this.</i>

939
00:53:15.988 --> 00:53:18.906
<i>And I was thinking that there were
plenty of assholes just like them</i>

940
00:53:18.907 --> 00:53:21.617
<i>in the neighborhood. with
houses just like this.</i>

941
00:53:21.618 --> 00:53:25.162
<i>filled with expensive shit just like
this that would never be missed.</i>

942
00:53:25.163 --> 00:53:28.541
<i>Piles of forgotten wealth
just lying around in drawers</i>

943
00:53:28.542 --> 00:53:30.793
<i>where they were doing
no one any good.</i>

944
